Central Bank of Kenya Plans to Sell 2 Billion Shilling of Reverse Repos

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-04-06T08:44:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/central-bank-of-kenya-plans-to-sell-2-billion-shilling-of-reverse-repos.html
The Central Bank of  Kenya  will sell
2 billion shillings ($24 million) of reverse repuchase
agreements today, according to a statement from the Nairobi-
based bank.  In a reverse-repo agreement, central banks lend securities
for a set period, temporarily draining cash from the banking
system. At maturity, the securities are returned to the bank and
the cash to traders.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  